This is so far the most effective yet affordable oil cleanser to have in your skincare wishlist. It gently removes all the excess oil and dirts on my face, although it's not powerful enough to remove waterproof make up. It doesn't irritate my skin at all, really worth the price!

7. Nivea Soothing Cleansing Oil with Grape Seed Currently I use Nivea as everybody compliments it such a nice cheap oil cleanser, I end up bought this one. Available in two variants, I choose the grape seed oil as it is good for oily combination skin like mine than coconut oil https://t.co/PWB4cJ6ySI

Derived naturally from blackcurrant seed oil and black soybean oil, it has lighter texture than Laneige with a really great performance in melting away the sebum, blackheads and whiteheads. This is for me such a perfect, homey cleansing oil that never causes any breakouts👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻

6. Dear Klairs Gentle Black Deep Cleansing Oil Another Korean brand put in my wishlist goes to Dear Klairs. I like their simple idea of creating good quality products using only necessary ingredients that don't irritate skin. This gentle oil cleanser is one of their best seller. https://t.co/w6LQfNDsz5

Is it worth the money? Well, I could say it depends on your budget😂 if you search for a very good quality multi level oil cleanser especially to reduce your blackheads and sebum, you will get the job satisfied with this one. For me, this product is absolutely worth every penny.

It is a glide-on oil type cleanser and completely melts away the blackheads and whiteheads while leaving your skin supple and smooth. When you emulsify the oil, it turns milky then you rinse your face with lukewarm water. It feels so good and helps me to get rid of clogged pores. https://t.co/sTaci99nE9

5. Laneige Perfect Pore Cleansing Oil Move to the next brand as I get addicted to oil-based cleanser😂 let me introduce you to one of the best cleansing oil from Laneige! This is absolutely good not only for make up remover, but also for taking away blackheads and excess sebum. https://t.co/xz8KfzOo5X

I never get any breakouts or any negative effects in applying this product. I think this is good for all skin type since the formula is very gentle. In addition, this product is also available in a mini size so it will help you to try this before deciding to buy the full size🎉. https://t.co/us1H4vqpKs

During the time I used this oil cleanser, I can say that this gently dissolve my make up, SPF and all the dirts on my face without leaving an oily residue and greasy feeling thanks to its lightweight texture. No fragrance, no mineral oil and no paraben are another good points.

4. Innisfree Apple Seed Cleansing Oil My very first cleansing oil comes from Innisfree, a nature-oriented skincare and cosmetic brand. Its ingredients come from natural derived plants in Jeju, South Korea. I then tried this oil cleanser and surprisingly, it suits my skin well! https://t.co/BEjfEYHhMI

After experiencing water-based cleanser, I then decide to switch to cleansing oil. I thought that oil cleanser tend to make my skin oilier, but in fact, it will cleanse your pores so well without feeling dry. It also protects the natural lipid layer and good bacteria of the skin.

Beside its disappointing remover power, I got something like a surf when I rubbed my face using this. The soaked cotton will release the surf and it did disturbing. I never heard this thing at all when I read reviews from some friends and beauty vloggers so it was shocking me.

3. Garnier Micellar Cleansing Water What would I say about this product is regardless of its friendly budget price, I don't think it suits me best. When I soaked up the cotton pad with this micellar water and applied it to my face, I felt that it didn't cleanse my face so well. https://t.co/7y2rswNLuN

Talking about its cons, the only thing that everyone complains about is obviously its price😂 Personally, I don't mind with that as it defines best quality at best price. It's really worth the hype and available in various size, from small to give a try to big ones used at home. https://t.co/1vyc5aGlRP

So far, I am quite impressed with its performance in removing make up, excess oil and all impurities on my skin. It cleanses my face perfectly without extra power to swipe using cotton pad. Once you have a right clean face, it minimizes the risk of having acne or clogged pores.

2. Bioderma Sensibio H2O Micellar Water This is definitely my holy grail of micellar water of all the time. As you know, Bioderma as a French dermatological expertise is a pioneer of micellar water. A forefront of innovation, Bioderma is a leader in this typical watery product. https://t.co/ujGA4ObEIo

For its bad side, I don't think it will be as much as its good side. Maybe it will be easier for me personally to grab the travel size if I go somewhere as The Saem Cleansing Water is only available in 300 ml such a big size that only can be used at home for your routine.

The good side, The Saem Cleansing Water has a very affordable price for its big size, so it lasts longer to be used daily comparing with other Korean cleansing water brand. In addition, it doesn't irritate my skin and doesn't give any negative effect since I have sensitive skin.

1. The Saem Healing Tea Garden Cleansing Water This is my very first cleansing water when I learn to take care of my skin. I only tried two variants, green tea and white tea. Both of them gives me a clean feeling without any dryness before I continue to finish with facial wash. https://t.co/5nVdwvuWDF

Back to the topic after a long introduction😂. I use both oil-based cleanser and water-based cleanser as my first cleanser. I'd love to rub my face with cleansing oil to melt my make up and pollution residues; or sometimes I'll break them down with cotton pad and micellar water.

Double cleanse will definitely make sure you're getting every last stitch of make up, excess sebum and dirts off your face. And you will not over cleanse your face as oil-based cleanser will help to maintain your skin barrier while water-based remove all the residues in one way.

Basically, double cleanse for sure consists of first cleanser and second cleanser; first by using whether oil-based cleanser or water-based cleanser (ex. micellar water) while second cleanser is traditionally rinsing your face using your daily facial wash to get the job done.

When you heard 10 steps Korean skincare, double cleanse is definitely one of the very first thing to do to take away all impurities on your skin. Double cleanse is a method of cleansing your face twice. Sometimes we doubt: will double cleanse over-clean our face?

As I mentioned before in #Episode01 of my skincare journey (https://t.co/guiPgUd3aU) during these 3 years I put my trust in 10 steps Korean skincare. In these times, I tried many products for each steps of skincare. So for now, let's get started to review the first cleansers!🧚🏻‍♀️✨

I write this thread thanks to these support system: - Cho, Charlotte. 2015. The Little Book of Skincare. New York: Harper Collins - Molvar, Kari. 2016. https://t.co/xLfIMZMlJA. New York: NY Times - Best skincare buddy @FauziaSyifaa for all the reviews, advices and suggestions 💜

Thank you for being so patient & attentive to read this thread as my first glance😂 I will try my best to be as honest as possible in reviewing skincare products that I've been used for minimum 3 weeks. Please check the sources below as your reference #Episode01 #skincareroutine

From now on, since this tweet has been posted, I will write a review of one product for each thread. At least, based on my experience I will share you guys good and bad side of skincare products so hopefully it will enrich your knowledge in understanding more your skin #Episode01

The good news is, since my skin is well-moisturized enough, the problems that have been my concerns slowly but sure are gone. Well, I didn't say that my skin condition now is perfect cause still, I tend to fight against hyperpigmentation, redness and other sensitive skin issues.

There are cleanser, toner, moisturizer and sunscreen. Yap, I got this from some references that your skin might be not ready yet to soak the nutrition up tremendously in the beginning. As the time goes by, my skin has a well adaptation on this new routine so I continue to use it.

From that fact, I learn that I have dehydrated skin so yeah, I decide to try layering my skincare to keep its moisture. I didn't put skincare products on my skin directly with 10 products in one trial as my skin will need to adapt to this regime. First, I used 4 steps as a basic.

Previously, I thought that oily skin type doesn't need moisturizer since its excess of oil level. That was what came in my mind but day by day, I've grown up to know that rather oily or dry skin type, it indicates unbalanced moisture level that consequently cause dehydrated skin.

Once your skin has a right balance of moisture content from both water and oil level, it will lead you to have a supple, radiant and healthy look skin. All your skin problems in substance caused by one main reason: lack of moisture. Hence, moisture is everything that you need.

In the beginning, I'd love to read numerous blogs & reviews from beauty vlogger as my references about how to take care of your skin. Briefly, I found out that asian skincare routine tends to intensively focus on hydrating and moisturizing your skin to strength your skin barrier.

In the past, I did get rid of these problems: dullness, uneven skin tone, excess of sebum for my T-zone and dry patches in cheeks area. They made my skin looked lackluster and lost its glow. It was bad for a student who was still struggling for being graduated from university.

My skin has been improved a lot. FYI, I used to have normal skin until in my latest 20s it turns to combination sensitive skin (oily T-zone, drier U-zone) due to several factors such as pollution, instant foods, daily activities, and lack of knowledge for taking care of my skin.

So the question here is: "Why I decide to choose 10 steps Korean skincare as my daily routine?" Well, the reason is simple: My skin loves it. I know, it's quite shallow but hey, I got such a promising result after around a month of commitment, consistence & patience in using it.

Basically, this well-known method consists of: 1. First cleanser 2. Second cleanser (water based) 3. Exfoliator (once or twice a week) 4. Toner 5. Essence 6. Serum 7. Eye cream 8. Moisturizer 9. Sunscreen (for AM routine) 10. Mask (weekly treatment, depends on your skin type)

Long-short story, since 2017 I rely on a popular "10 steps Korean skin care". It's a method in which you use several skincare products to maintain the moisture level of your skin, as bright and glow look comes from a well-moisturized skin or "chok-chok" in Korean beauty term.

Hello! I would like to share my personal journey using skincare products start within this tweet. Please bear in mind that I'm not an aesthetician, dermatologist or skincare expert (or whatever you name it) cause I just wanna show you my experience to find the best skin products.
